{
  "texts": [
    "The kernel sizes for each convolutional layer range from 3 to 5, and each layer has 256 channels.",
    "In order to identify clinical data that was considerably class-imbalanced and forecast the development www.nature.com/scientificreports/ of coronary heart disease (CHD), a study done in 38 developed an effective neural network using convolutional layers.",
    "For the purpose of predicting CVD, we classified the Cleveland dataset using this model.",
    "The size of the convolutional kernels is kept to (kernel-size = 3), and (pool-size = 2).",
    "The dropout rate for regularization is kept to (dropout-rate = 0.2)."
  ]
}